        <h1>Welcome to the Haus</h1>
        <br />
        <span style=
        "font:18px Times-Bold; font-weight:bold; font-weight:bold;">
        “</span><span style="font-size:16px; font-weight:bold;">The
        Codehaus</span><span style=
        "font:18px Times-Bold; font-weight:bold; font-weight:bold;">”</span>
        is a collaborative environment for building opensource
        projects with a strong emphasis on modern languages,
        focussed on quality components that meet real world needs.
        <br />
        <br />
        We believe in open source as a pragmatic approach to
        software development, and all our projects have <a href=
        "customs/licenses.html"
             rel="self"
             title="Licenses">business-friendly licences</a>.
        <br />
        <br />
        Enjoy your stay at the Haus!
        <br />
        <br />

        <h1>Explore the Haus</h1>Take a look at our <a href=
        "featured.html"
             rel="self"
             title="Featured Project - Boo">featured project -
             Boo</a>
        <br />
        <br />
        If that doesn’t take your fancy; then take a look through
        some of our other <a href="resources.html"
             rel="self"
             title="Resources">starting points</a>.
        <br />
        <br />

        <h1>Research the Haus</h1>See the <a href=
        "support/faq.html"
             rel="self"
             title="FAQ">FAQ</a>.
        <br />
        <br />
        See our <a href="customs/manifesto.html"
             rel="self"
             title="Manifesto">Manifesto</a> and <a href=
             "customs/selection.html"
             rel="self"
             title="Project Selection">Project Selection</a>
             guidelines.
        <br />
        <br />

        <h1>Join the Haus</h1>If you want to join an existing
        project, then you should signup using <a href=
        "xircles/index.html"
             rel="self"
             title="Xircles">Xircles</a>. Once you’ve signed up
             you’ll be able to apply for membership to projects or
             create your own.
        <br />
        <br />
        If you want to migrate a project to Codehaus, then you
        should review the <a href="customs/selection.html"
             rel="self"
             title="Project Selection">project selection
             criteria</a> and project migration guidelines.
        <br />
        <br />
        <br />

        <h1>Support the Haus</h1>If you want to <a href=
        "supporters/advertising.html"
             rel="self"
             title="Advertising">support the Haus</a>, then we
             can't encourage you enough!
        <br />
